Plot the estimated known outcomes, as well as the raw data

Source: R/plot_known_outcomes.R
plot_known_outcomes.Rd

Produces a simple plot, using base R, of the raw case and death time-series data, as well as the estimated number of known outcomes on each day.

Usage

plot_known_outcomes(df_in)

Arguments

df_in

A data.frame of the format returned by known_outcomes().

Value

A plot of the three time-series on the same plot, with a legend

Examples

# Load Ebola 1976 outbreak data
data("ebola1976")

onset_to_death_ebola <- epiparameter::epidist_db(
  disease = "Ebola Virus Disease",
  epi_dist = "onset_to_death",
  author = "Barry_etal"
)
#> Using Barry et al. (2018) <10.1016/S0140-6736(18)31387-4> PMID: 30047375. 
#> To retrieve the short citation use the 'get_citation' function

df_known_outcomes <- known_outcomes(
  df_in = ebola1976,
  epi_dist = onset_to_death_ebola
)

plot_known_outcomes(df_known_outcomes)
